layout: base.njk
title: About
permalink: /about/index.html
---

<section class="section">
  <div class="about-split">
    <div>
      <h1>About This Site</h1>

      <p class="prose-width">
        Exonumist is a collector-focused reference site built around cataloged New York City
        transportation tokens while also documenting unlisted material, patterns, oddities, errors,
        counterfeits, and related pieces that deserve long-term visibility.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <h3>Site Focus</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Listed NYC transportation tokens</li>
        <li>Unlisted discoveries</li>
        <li>Errors & oddities</li>
        <li>Collector research</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="about-split">
    <div>
      <h2>My Collection</h2>

      <p class="prose-width">
        While this site currently focuses on New York City transportation exonumia, my broader collection
        includes Arcade, Hard Times, Civil War, Merchant, and Miscellaneous tokens — basically, interesting
        shiny metal things with history behind them.
      </p>

      <p class="prose-width">
        Listed transportation material follows the Atwood-Coffee Catalogue where applicable. Unlisted items
        are included when they help document discoveries, varieties, errors, oddities, or related collecting
        areas.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <h3>Also Collecting</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Civil War tokens</li>
        <li>Hard Times tokens</li>
        <li>Merchant tokens</li>
        <li>Arcade tokens</li>
        <li>Miscellaneous exonumia</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="want-list">
  <h2>Want List</h2>

  <p class="section-intro">
    I am actively looking for certain pieces for the collection, especially early New York
    transportation tokens, undocumented material, unusual varieties, and better examples of
    pieces already represented here.
  </p>

  {% set wantedTokens = [] %}
  {% for token in collections.officialAll %}
    {% if token.wanted %}
      {% set wantedTokens = wantedTokens.concat([token]) %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}

  {% if wantedTokens.length %}
    <h3>Currently Seeking</h3>

    <div class="wanted-token-list">
      {% for token in wantedTokens %}
        <a class="wanted-token-link" href="/official/{{ token.displayId | lower }}/">
          <strong>{{ token.displayId }}</strong>
          <span>{{ token.title }}</span>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% endif %}

  <p class="section-intro">
    I am also interested in New York transportation tokens, Civil War tokens, Hard Times tokens,
    merchant tokens, arcade tokens, trade tokens, and other historically interesting exonumia.
  </p>

  <p class="section-intro">
    Have something available for sale or trade?
    <a href="mailto:YOUR_EMAIL_HERE">Contact me</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Research & References</h2>

  <p class="section-intro">
    References and organizations useful for transportation token research and catalog information.
  </p>

  <div class="grid-narrow">
    {% for resource in resources | sort(attribute="order") %}
      {% if resource.pub %}
        <a class="card-link" href="{{ resource.urlRef | resolveUrlRef(site) }}">
          <article class="resource-card resource-card-with-media">
            <div class="resource-card-body">
              <strong>{{ resource.title }}</strong>
              <p>{{ resource.text }}</p>
            </div>

            {% if resource.image %}
              <div class="resource-card-media">
                <img
                  class="resource-card-logo"
                  src="{{ resource.image }}"
                  alt="{{ resource.title }}" />
              </div>
            {% endif %}
          </article>
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
